<graph edgedefault="undirected"><node id="&quot;BEES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Bees are a group of insects known for producing honey and living in colonies, often confused with other insects due to similar appearances."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees are a group of insects that form a colony and are sensitive to vibrations and movements near their hive."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees are described as having specific preferences and behaviors regarding different types of foundation and frames."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees are insects known for their role in pollination and honey production, and they can react inconsistently to disturbances."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees are insects that live in hives, perform various tasks, and respond to stimuli in specific ways."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees are responsible for drawing out the foundation and building cells within the beehive."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees are the members of the colony, responsible for various tasks such as foraging and pollination."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees are the primary subjects of management and care in beekeeping, forming the core of the hive."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees are the workers of the hive, responsible for producing honey, maintaining the colony, and pollinating plants."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees refer to a colony of honeybees, managed by beekeepers, known for their complex social structure and behavior."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-fd2ef96a08268bf831497844fff694b4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0c33d64a7162702d929065af1c959dea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-314ae8e8df408e418608c7ade21dd41b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4b3f4041222f1f92f07432b13f712f21&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f6ba5eccbc91a96e671b14d79ed74ba3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d5b1917950dbf98fe0b5ce38e219280a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0cae971b0b2192812c441da52ef3cf20&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3dbda77a0a0cb04439105e3ecd8449b4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-075e0d9993c009051cdcd78e585e5e63&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-756b79c60c8a46adc993db79dc6aa966</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 31}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 79}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HIVE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A Hive is a structure where bees live and store honey, often managed by beekeepers."&lt;SEP&gt;"A hive is the structure where bees live and produce honey, managed by beekeepers."&lt;SEP&gt;"A hive is the structure where bees live and produce honey."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hive is a structure where bees live and work, providing shelter and a place for the colony to function."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hive is the general term for the beehive structure where bees live and work."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hive is the living space and workplace for the bees, where they perform various tasks such as brood rearing and foraging."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hive is the structure where bees live and store honey, and it is sensitive to external vibrations and movements."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hive is the structure where the bees live and work."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hive is the structure where the colony lives and grows."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hive refers to a colony of bees, managed by beekeepers for honey production or pollination services."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hive refers to a structure where bees live and produce honey, managed by beekeepers."&lt;SEP&gt;"The hive is the structure where the bees live and work, and it is the focus of the weekly visits and observations."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-fd2ef96a08268bf831497844fff694b4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0c33d64a7162702d929065af1c959dea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bbe65f20246fcdba1ffce44cd00d77cc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4b3f4041222f1f92f07432b13f712f21&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f6ba5eccbc91a96e671b14d79ed74ba3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d5b1917950dbf98fe0b5ce38e219280a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0cae971b0b2192812c441da52ef3cf20&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3dbda77a0a0cb04439105e3ecd8449b4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-075e0d9993c009051cdcd78e585e5e63&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-756b79c60c8a46adc993db79dc6aa966&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fe8cd55e58ac3503bfa933ac21c4169c</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 28}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 77}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PERSON&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A Person is an individual who needs to act around bees and work with them, following specific guidelines to avoid attracting their attention."&lt;SEP&gt;"Person refers to any individual or entity that can hold subscription rights or similar rights to equity interests."&lt;SEP&gt;"Person refers to any individual who is a party to the agreements or transactions, including directors and other stakeholders."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0c33d64a7162702d929065af1c959dea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f6e13d16c15abf29f71b861a4a727499&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-db9abea29c67ef8a62191c828a65bcb9</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 30}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RINGS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Rings are accessories worn on fingers that can be shiny and reflective, attracting bees due to their movement and appearance in sunlight."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0c33d64a7162702d929065af1c959dea</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 30}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WRISTWATCH&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A Wristwatch is a wearable accessory that can be shiny and reflective, attracting bees due to its movement and appearance in sunlight."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0c33d64a7162702d929065af1c959dea</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 30}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BROAD STAND OR PLATFORM&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A Broad Stand or Platform is a stable base on which a hive is placed, providing stability and space for bee activity."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0c33d64a7162702d929065af1c959dea</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 28}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 77}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BANANA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A Banana is a fruit that the person was eating near the hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0c33d64a7162702d929065af1c959dea</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 30}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SUBSTRATE VIBRATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Substrate Vibration is the way bees feel vibrations through the ground or hive structure, which can influence their behavior."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0c33d64a7162702d929065af1c959dea</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 30}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SUNLIGHT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ENVIRONMENTAL CONDITION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Sunlight is a factor that can make shiny objects, like rings and wristwatches, more visible to bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0c33d64a7162702d929065af1c959dea</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 30}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BEEKEEPER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A Beekeeper is someone who manages and cares for beehives."&lt;SEP&gt;"A beekeeper is a person who manages and cares for bee colonies, often for the purpose of harvesting honey or studying bee behavior."&lt;SEP&gt;"A beekeeper is someone experienced in handling bees, capable of providing guidance and insight into beekeeping challenges."&lt;SEP&gt;"A beekeeper is someone who manages and cares for bee colonies, often learning and building during the first year."&lt;SEP&gt;"A beekeeper is someone who manages and cares for beehives."&lt;SEP&gt;"Beekeeper is a person who manages and cares for bee colonies, often working closely with hives."&lt;SEP&gt;"Beekeeper is a person who studies and manages bees, particularly focusing on honey bees as a subject of study."&lt;SEP&gt;"Beekeeper is the person responsible for managing the hive, conducting inspections, and ensuring the health and productivity of the bees."&lt;SEP&gt;"Beekeepers are responsible for adhering to state-specific laws and regulations regarding beekeeping and importation."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-480675c7bf17efa7e8ffb90c77a84ea3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bbe65f20246fcdba1ffce44cd00d77cc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-04c42078277d71b7abaf2963a3bbbf25&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4b3f4041222f1f92f07432b13f712f21&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f6ba5eccbc91a96e671b14d79ed74ba3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d5b1917950dbf98fe0b5ce38e219280a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0cae971b0b2192812c441da52ef3cf20&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3dbda77a0a0cb04439105e3ecd8449b4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-075e0d9993c009051cdcd78e585e5e63</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 28}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 78}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PROPOLIS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Propolis is a resin-like substance collected by Worker Bees from trees and used to seal gaps and maintain the Hive's structural integrity."&lt;SEP&gt;"Propolis is a resin-like substance collected by bees and used to seal gaps in the hive, which can affect the movement of the hive cover."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-bbe65f20246fcdba1ffce44cd00d77cc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0cae971b0b2192812c441da52ef3cf20</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 39}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;OUTER COVER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Outer cover is a part of the hive that can be glued down by propolis and needs to be handled carefully to avoid disturbing the bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0cae971b0b2192812c441da52ef3cf20</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 39}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VIBRATIONS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Vibrations are movements transmitted through the hive that can affect the bees' behavior and comfort."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0cae971b0b2192812c441da52ef3cf20</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 29}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;STAND&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Stand is a base or platform on which the hive is placed, affecting how vibrations are transmitted."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0cae971b0b2192812c441da52ef3cf20</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PROPOLIS GLUE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Propolis glue is a substance used to secure the outer cover of the hive, which can affect how vibrations are transmitted."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0cae971b0b2192812c441da52ef3cf20</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 39}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WORKING AREA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Working area is the space where beekeepers perform tasks, and their movements can affect the bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0cae971b0b2192812c441da52ef3cf20</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 29}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PROPOLIS BUILDUP&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONDITION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Propolis buildup is a condition where propolis accumulates, affecting the movement of hive components."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0cae971b0b2192812c441da52ef3cf20</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 29}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SETTLING DOWN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Settling down is a state where bees calm down after being disturbed."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0cae971b0b2192812c441da52ef3cf20</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 31}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 79}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BAD DAYS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Bad days refer to periods when bees are more likely to react negatively to disturbances."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0cae971b0b2192812c441da52ef3cf20</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 29}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;THUMPING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ACTION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Thumping is a specific type of movement that can transmit vibrations to the hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0cae971b0b2192812c441da52ef3cf20</data>
</node>
