</node>
<node id="&quot;CLOSING UP THE HIVE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ACTION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Closing up the hive is a specific action that can help manage bee behavior."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0cae971b0b2192812c441da52ef3cf20</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CONTINUE WORKING LATER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ACTION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Continuing to work later is a strategy to manage bee behavior."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0cae971b0b2192812c441da52ef3cf20</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;UPWARD WHACK&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ACTION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"An upward whack is a specific type of movement that can transmit vibrations to the hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0cae971b0b2192812c441da52ef3cf20</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FEW MINUTES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TIME"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Few minutes is a duration that can be used to allow bees to settle down."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0cae971b0b2192812c441da52ef3cf20</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ANOTHER TIME&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TIME"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Another time is a duration that can be used to schedule further work with bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0cae971b0b2192812c441da52ef3cf20</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WATCHING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ACTION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Watching is an action that an experienced beekeeper can perform to observe and guide a novice beekeeper."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0cae971b0b2192812c441da52ef3cf20</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;POINTING OUT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ACTION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Pointing out is an action that an experienced beekeeper can perform to provide guidance to a novice beekeeper."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0cae971b0b2192812c441da52ef3cf20</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GLUED DOWN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONDITION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Glued down is a condition where the outer cover of the hive is secured by propolis."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0cae971b0b2192812c441da52ef3cf20</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PERSISTENT BANGING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONDITION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Persistent banging is a condition where the hive is subjected to repeated vibrations."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0cae971b0b2192812c441da52ef3cf20</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HIVE MANAGEMENT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ACTIVITY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Hive management involves various actions to care for and maintain the health of the hive."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hive management is the overall process of caring for and maintaining the health of the hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0cae971b0b2192812c441da52ef3cf20</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BEE BEHAVIOR&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ACTIVITY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Bee behavior includes various actions and reactions of bees to their environment and interactions with humans."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bee behavior refers to the actions and activities of individual bees within the hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0cae971b0b2192812c441da52ef3cf20&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3dbda77a0a0cb04439105e3ecd8449b4</data>
