</node>
<node id="&quot;HIVE STAND&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Hive stand is a base or platform on which the hive is placed, affecting how vibrations are transmitted."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0cae971b0b2192812c441da52ef3cf20</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HIVE COVER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Hive cover is a part of the hive that can be manipulated to manage vibrations."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0cae971b0b2192812c441da52ef3cf20</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HIVE ENTRANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Hive Entrance is the opening of the beehive where bees enter and exit."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hive Entrance is the point of exit and entry for bees within the hive, used for orientation flights and other activities."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hive Entrance is the point of exit for worker bees when they leave the hive for orientation flights and foraging."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hive entrance is the opening through which bees enter and exit the hive, and it can be affected by vibrations."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6b4933e28419676b4dc2c84fef33d751&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0cae971b0b2192812c441da52ef3cf20&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9dbacd73c4d0e9e9182787aaaced95eb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-975d760faa24c8acc201aa85031cdd0a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HIVE INTERIOR&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Hive interior is the internal space of the hive where bees live and store honey, and it can be affected by vibrations."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0cae971b0b2192812c441da52ef3cf20</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HIVE EXTERIOR&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Hive exterior is the external space around the hive, and it can be affected by vibrations."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0cae971b0b2192812c441da52ef3cf20</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HIVE FOUNDATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"STRUCTURE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Hive foundation is the base structure of the hive, and it can be affected by vibrations."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0cae971b0b2192812c441da52ef3cf20</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HIVE WALLS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"STRUCTURE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Hive walls are the sides of the hive, and they can be affected by vibrations."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0cae971b0b2192812c441da52ef3cf20</data>
</node>
