</node>
<node id="&quot;PACKAGE BEES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Package Bees are a method of introducing new bees to a hive, often used by beginner beekeepers."&lt;SEP&gt;"Package Bees is a commercial product containing about 10,000 bees, including workers, a few drones, and a queen, used for bee installation."&lt;SEP&gt;"Package bees are a type of bee colony sold commercially for beekeeping purposes."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-04c42078277d71b7abaf2963a3bbbf25&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-920509d6d494100a9a9f22a446af9adb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-301bd1c4c4db829c203622d95e222ecf</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 38}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;STATES WITH APIARY INSPECTION PROGRAMS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"States with Apiary Inspection Programs refer to regions that regulate beekeeping to some extent, often expanding their scope of regulation."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-301bd1c4c4db829c203622d95e222ecf</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MUNICIPALITIES WITH BEEKEEPING CODES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Municipalities with Beekeeping Codes are local governments that have imposed their own regulations on beekeeping, primarily in the form of bans or restrictions."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-301bd1c4c4db829c203622d95e222ecf</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HONEY BEE BROOD DISEASES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Honey Bee Brood Diseases are specific health issues affecting bee colonies, particularly contagious ones that can lead to colony demise."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-301bd1c4c4db829c203622d95e222ecf</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PARASITIC MITES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Parasitic Mites are non-native pests that have been in North America since the mid-1980s and pose a significant threat to honey bee colonies."&lt;SEP&gt;"Parasitic Mites are pests that can severely impact honey bee colonies, causing significant harm."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8eac26b677de38a4280bbf0546123920&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-301bd1c4c4db829c203622d95e222ecf</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;AFRICANIZED BEES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Africanized Bees are a type of bee that pose a serious threat to humans due to their aggressive behavior."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-301bd1c4c4db829c203622d95e222ecf</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HONEY BEE COLONIES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Honey Bee Colonies are the primary focus of the text, facing threats from diseases and mites."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8eac26b677de38a4280bbf0546123920</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;AFRICANIZED BEE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Africanized Bee is described as a potentially serious threat to humans."&lt;SEP&gt;"Africanized bees are a type of bee known for their aggressive behavior and are spreading, leading to increased regulation."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-480675c7bf17efa7e8ffb90c77a84ea3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8eac26b677de38a4280bbf0546123920</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 15}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 69}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;STATE BUDGETS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"State Budgets refer to the financial allocations of state governments, which have been cut due to economic conditions."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8eac26b677de38a4280bbf0546123920</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FEDERAL BUDGETS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Federal Budgets refer to the financial allocations of the federal government, which have been cut due to economic conditions."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8eac26b677de38a4280bbf0546123920</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BEE INSPECTION PROGRAMS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Bee Inspection Programs are part of the budget cuts affecting beekeeping, impacting the ability to monitor and control diseases and mites."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8eac26b677de38a4280bbf0546123920</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BEEKEEPERS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Beekeepers are individuals responsible for managing honey bee colonies and are expected to recognize, control, or eliminate diseases and mites."&lt;SEP&gt;"Beekeepers refer to individuals or groups managing bee colonies, often sharing common practices and standards."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-fd2ef96a08268bf831497844fff694b4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8eac26b677de38a4280bbf0546123920</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 6}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 49}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HIGHER AUTHORITY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Higher Authority refers to external entities that beekeepers traditionally rely on to solve their problems."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8eac26b677de38a4280bbf0546123920</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FEDERAL LAWS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Federal Laws include the ban on importing live bees, which is the only regulation mentioned at the federal level."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8eac26b677de38a4280bbf0546123920</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;QUEEN BEES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Queen Bees are used to introduce mites into the country, violating the federal ban on importing live bees."&lt;SEP&gt;"Queen bees are used in beekeeping and were likely imported illegally, causing legal violations."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-480675c7bf17efa7e8ffb90c77a84ea3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8eac26b677de38a4280bbf0546123920</data>
