  <data key="d2">chunk-402377454165587ae1b3b0fcc502ff15</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;AMERICAN SOCIETY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"American society refers to the social and cultural context in which burlesque musicals operate and have an impact."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-402377454165587ae1b3b0fcc502ff15</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;THEATERS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Theaters are venues where burlesque musicals are performed."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-402377454165587ae1b3b0fcc502ff15</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TOURS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Tours refer to the traveling performances of burlesque musicals across different locations."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-402377454165587ae1b3b0fcc502ff15</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BURLESQUE MUSICAL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Burlesque Musical is a type of theatrical performance characterized by its humorous distortion of fact, fantastical drollery, and musical embellishment. It was popular in the late 19th century."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-2d69e4328e8230799222e9f1c6bf179b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;EXTRAVAGANZA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Extravaganza is another form of theatrical performance that allows for any extravagances or whimsicalities without a definite purpose. It is less focused on meaning and more on spectacle."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-2d69e4328e8230799222e9f1c6bf179b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GILBERT AND SULLIVAN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Gilbert and Sullivan refers to the collaborative duo W.S. Gilbert and Arthur Sullivan, known for their comedic, melodic operettas that set new standards for composition and professionalism."&lt;SEP&gt;"Gilbert and Sullivan refers to the collaborative partnership between British playwright William Gilbert and British composer Arthur Sullivan, known for their comedic, melodic operettas that set a new standard for composition and professionalism in music theater."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-2d69e4328e8230799222e9f1c6bf179b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a4ea09918bfcff4afd764d28115b826d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WILLIAM GILBERT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"William Gilbert is a British playwright who, along with Arthur Sullivan, co-founded the Gilbert and Sullivan collaboration, creating a series of successful operettas."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-2d69e4328e8230799222e9f1c6bf179b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ARTHUR SULLIVAN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Arthur Sullivan is a British composer who, along with William Gilbert, co-founded the Gilbert and Sullivan collaboration, creating a series of successful operettas."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-2d69e4328e8230799222e9f1c6bf179b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VARIETY SHOWS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Variety Shows were the most popular forms of music theater in Britain during the 1860s, featuring a wide range of acts including music, comedy, and acrobatics."&lt;SEP&gt;"Variety shows were popular forms of music theater in Britain during the 1860s before Gilbert and Sullivan's influence."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-2d69e4328e8230799222e9f1c6bf179b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a4ea09918bfcff4afd764d28115b826d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FRENCH OPERETTAS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"French Operettas were a popular form of music theater in Britain during the 1860s, known for their light-hearted and romantic themes."&lt;SEP&gt;"French operettas were popular forms of music theater in Britain during the 1860s before Gilbert and Sullivan's influence."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-2d69e4328e8230799222e9f1c6bf179b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a4ea09918bfcff4afd764d28115b826d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COMIC LIGHT OPERAS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Comic Light Operas were a popular form of music theater in Britain during the 1860s, combining elements of comedy and music."&lt;SEP&gt;"Comic light operas were popular forms of music theater in Britain during the 1860s before Gilbert and Sullivan's influence."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-2d69e4328e8230799222e9f1c6bf179b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a4ea09918bfcff4afd764d28115b826d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BRITISH PLAYWRIGHT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ROLE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"British Playwright refers to William Gilbert, a playwright known for his work with Arthur Sullivan."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-2d69e4328e8230799222e9f1c6bf179b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BRITISH COMPOSER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ROLE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"British Composer refers to Arthur Sullivan, a composer known for his work with William Gilbert."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-2d69e4328e8230799222e9f1c6bf179b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LATE 19TH CENTURY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TIME_PERIOD"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Late 19th Century refers to the period from approximately 1860 to 1900, during which various forms of music theater flourished."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-2d69e4328e8230799222e9f1c6bf179b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;AMERICA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"America refers to the United States of America, where Gilbert and Sullivan's operettas had a significant cultural impact and influenced American musical theater."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a4ea09918bfcff4afd764d28115b826d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HMS PINAFORE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"HMS Pinafore is a groundbreaking operetta by Gilbert and Sullivan that caused a craze known as 'Pinafore-Mania' in the United States."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a4ea09918bfcff4afd764d28115b826d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PINAFORE-MANIA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Pinafore-Mania refers to the widespread enthusiasm and popularity of HMS Pinafore in the United States, leading to frequent performances and a significant cultural impact."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a4ea09918bfcff4afd764d28115b826d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LARRY HART&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Larry Hart is an American lyricist who credits the work of Gilbert as a heavy influence on his own work."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a4ea09918bfcff4afd764d28115b826d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ALLEN JAY LERNER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Allen Jay Lerner is an American lyricist who credits the work of Gilbert as a heavy influence on his own work."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a4ea09918bfcff4afd764d28115b826d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;STEPHEN SONDHEIM&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Stephen Sondheim is an American composer and lyricist who credits the work of Gilbert as a heavy influence on his own work."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a4ea09918bfcff4afd764d28115b826d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CHARLES M. BARRAS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Charles M. Barras is the playwright who wrote _The Black Crook_, one of the earliest and most influential musicals in American theater history."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a4ea09918bfcff4afd764d28115b826d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;_THE BLACK CROOK_&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"_The Black Crook_ is a musical that opened in New York City in 1866 and is considered one of the earliest and most influential musicals in American theater history."&lt;SEP&gt;"_The Black Crook_ is a musical written by Charles M. Barras that opened in New York City in 1866 and is considered one of the earliest and most influential musicals in American theater history."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a4ea09918bfcff4afd764d28115b826d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NIBLO'S GARDEN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Niblo's Garden is a theater in Manhattan where _The Black Crook_ premiered in 1866."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a4ea09918bfcff4afd764d28115b826d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WILLIAM WHEATLEY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"William Wheatley is a producer of a theatrical production called 'The Black Crook', known for its significant run and historical importance in the American musical genre."&lt;SEP&gt;"William Wheatley is the producer of _The Black Crook_, which opened at Niblo's Garden in 1866."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a4ea09918bfcff4afd764d28115b826d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4a044eb6c9ea43a457fda3a5ae087892</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GEORGE BICKWELL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"George Bickwell composed the music for 'The Black Crook', contributing to its unique blend of French and German Romantic styles."&lt;SEP&gt;"George Bickwell is the composer of the music for _The Black Crook_, which opened at Niblo's Garden in 1866."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a4ea09918bfcff4afd764d28115b826d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4a044eb6c9ea43a457fda3a5ae087892</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DAVID COSTA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"David Costa choreographed 'The Black Crook', adding a layer of dance and movement to the production."&lt;SEP&gt;"David Costa is the choreographer of _The Black Crook_, which opened at Niblo's Garden in 1866."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a4ea09918bfcff4afd764d28115b826d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4a044eb6c9ea43a457fda3a5ae087892</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BRITAIN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Britain refers to the United Kingdom, where variety shows, French operettas, and comic light operas were popular before Gilbert and Sullivan's influence."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a4ea09918bfcff4afd764d28115b826d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;1860S&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The 1860s is a period during which variety shows, French operettas, and comic light operas were popular in Britain before Gilbert and Sullivan's influence."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a4ea09918bfcff4afd764d28115b826d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MANHATTAN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Manhattan is the borough where Niblo's Garden, the theater where _The Black Crook_ premiered, is located."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a4ea09918bfcff4afd764d28115b826d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;1866&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"1866 is the year when _The Black Crook_ premiered at Niblo's Garden in New York City."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a4ea09918bfcff4afd764d28115b826d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;1868&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"1868 is the year when _The Black Crook_ closed after running a total of 475 performances."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a4ea09918bfcff4afd764d28115b826d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;475 PERFORMANCES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"475 performances is the number of shows _The Black Crook_ ran before closing on January 4, 1868."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a4ea09918bfcff4afd764d28115b826d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;JANUARY 4, 1868&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"January 4, 1868 is the date when _The Black Crook_ closed after running 475 performances."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a4ea09918bfcff4afd764d28115b826d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;THE BLACK CROOK&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The Black Crook is a theatrical production that ran for 475 performances and is often considered the first American musical, combining elements of French and German Romantic styles."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-4a044eb6c9ea43a457fda3a5ae087892</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NEW YORK'S ACADEMY OF MUSIC&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"New York's Academy of Music was a venue that suffered a fire, leading to the creation of 'The Black Crook' as an alternative performance format."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-4a044eb6c9ea43a457fda3a5ae087892</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HENRY JARRETT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Henry Jarrett was a promoter involved in the production of 'The Black Crook' after the fire at New York's Academy of Music."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-4a044eb6c9ea43a457fda3a5ae087892</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HARRY PALMER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Harry Palmer was another promoter involved in the production of 'The Black Crook' after the fire at New York's Academy of Music."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-4a044eb6c9ea43a457fda3a5ae087892</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;JACQUES MONOD&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Jacques Monod is a scientist who survived a shipwreck and later became a co-founder of molecular biology."&lt;SEP&gt;"Jacques Monod was a young zoologist who participated in polar expeditions and conducted scientific studies, including an ethnographic study among the Inuit in Greenland."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-25f00c3248398c4a1ee9d6ee34da4f4f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4a044eb6c9ea43a457fda3a5ae087892</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CHARCOT'S TEAM&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Charcot's team is a group of experienced sailors led by Charcot, conducting a two-month-long adventure to the Arctic."&lt;SEP&gt;"Charcot's team refers to the group led by Jean-Martin Charcot, a renowned physician and explorer, who Jacques Monod joined for polar expeditions."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d2310f4a93312842679f6bf2bc19bef9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4a044eb6c9ea43a457fda3a5ae087892</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ANGMAGSSALIK&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Angmagssalik is a village in Greenland where some university students were dropped off as part of an ethnographic study."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-4a044eb6c9ea43a457fda3a5ae087892</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GREENLAND&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Greenland is a large island in the Arctic region where the ship aimed to sail and encountered ice fields."&lt;SEP&gt;"Greenland is a location where the Pourquoi-Pas? delivered supplies before encountering a storm."&lt;SEP&gt;"Greenland is the destination of Jacques Monod's polar expedition, where he conducted various scientific studies and lived among the Inuit for a year."&lt;SEP&gt;"Greenland is the destination of the expedition where Monod and his companions conducted their research."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-63e33f9f93ff598ff524cdfedd33db4b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d2310f4a93312842679f6bf2bc19bef9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-25f00c3248398c4a1ee9d6ee34da4f4f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4a044eb6c9ea43a457fda3a5ae087892</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;POLAR EXPEDITION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A polar expedition is a journey undertaken by Jacques Monod and his team to explore and study the Arctic region, including living among the Inuit and conducting scientific research."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-4a044eb6c9ea43a457fda3a5ae087892</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;JEAN-MARTIN CHARCOT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Jean-Martin Charcot was a renowned physician and explorer who led a team that Jacques Monod joined for polar expeditions."</data>
