  <data key="d2">chunk-d2310f4a93312842679f6bf2bc19bef9</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MONOD&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Monod is a researcher who proposed the theory of constitutive mutants, suggesting that the internal inducer would be produced and the enzyme would be made constitutively when a normal copy and a mutant copy of the gene are put together in the same bacterial cell."&lt;SEP&gt;"Monod is a scientist who collected samples of coastal marine life and climbed mountains around the fjord during a research expedition."&lt;SEP&gt;"Monod is a scientist who led a team in studying bacterial mutations and the regulation of β-galactosidase production."&lt;SEP&gt;"Monod is a scientist whose logic regarding enzyme regulation was later found to be faulty by François Jacob."&lt;SEP&gt;"Monod is an experienced sailor but an amateur compared to Charcot's team, having left his research at the Sorbonne to join Charcot's expedition."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-63e33f9f93ff598ff524cdfedd33db4b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e7d6b6d997e586818de66d4803488241&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d2310f4a93312842679f6bf2bc19bef9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9762f0ff2690cb73681a54a57f2e9170&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b2b3ed969d34b9c50bfc385bc325780</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SORBONNE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Sorbonne is a prestigious university in Paris where Monod conducted his research before joining the expedition."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d2310f4a93312842679f6bf2bc19bef9</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FAROE ISLANDS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
