<node id="&quot;COLONY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Colony is the group of bees living together in a hive, working collectively."&lt;SEP&gt;"Colony is the group of bees living together in the hive, with specific roles and responsibilities."&lt;SEP&gt;"Colony refers to a group of bees living together in a hive, which is the focus of management and observation throughout the text."&lt;SEP&gt;"Colony refers to the established group of people in the context of the beekeeping scenario."&lt;SEP&gt;"The colony is a bee colony that needs to be monitored for its progress and readiness for winter."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9dbacd73c4d0e9e9182787aaaced95eb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-975d760faa24c8acc201aa85031cdd0a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d5b1917950dbf98fe0b5ce38e219280a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-756b79c60c8a46adc993db79dc6aa966&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fe8cd55e58ac3503bfa933ac21c4169c</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 1}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 22}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;STIMULUS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Stimulus is any factor that causes a response in a bee, such as movement or smell."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d5b1917950dbf98fe0b5ce38e219280a</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 37}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MOVEMENT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Movement is a form of stimulus that can cause bees to react, such as the approach of a beekeeper."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d5b1917950dbf98fe0b5ce38e219280a</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 37}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;APPROACH&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Approach is the act of moving towards the hive, which can be a stimulus for bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d5b1917950dbf98fe0b5ce38e219280a</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 37}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;YOUNG BEE DEVELOPMENT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Young Bee Development is the process of young bees growing and maturing within the hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d5b1917950dbf98fe0b5ce38e219280a</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 37}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PLANT REPRODUCTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Plant Reproduction is the result of pollination, leading to the growth of new plants."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d5b1917950dbf98fe0b5ce38e219280a</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 37}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COMMUNICATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Communication is the exchange of information between bees, often through pheromones."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d5b1917950dbf98fe0b5ce38e219280a</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 37}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PHEROMONES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Pheromones are chemical signals used by bees for communication and coordination."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d5b1917950dbf98fe0b5ce38e219280a</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 37}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COORDINATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Coordination is the ability of bees to work together efficiently within the hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d5b1917950dbf98fe0b5ce38e219280a</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 37}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HARVESTING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Harvesting is the process of collecting honey from the hive by beekeepers."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d5b1917950dbf98fe0b5ce38e219280a</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 37}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BEEKEEPING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ACTIVITY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Beekeeping is the practice of managing and caring for bee colonies, often for the purpose of harvesting honey or studying bee behavior."&lt;SEP&gt;"Beekeeping is the practice of managing hives and ensuring their health and productivity."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d5b1917950dbf98fe0b5ce38e219280a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3dbda77a0a0cb04439105e3ecd8449b4</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 38}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DRONE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Drone is a male bee whose primary role is to mate with the queen, and plays a critical but less frequent role in the hive compared to the worker bee."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-bbe65f20246fcdba1ffce44cd00d77cc</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 34}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;QUEEN BEE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Queen Bee is responsible for laying eggs and is essential for the continuation of the colony, though her role becomes routine after mating."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-bbe65f20246fcdba1ffce44cd00d77cc</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 33}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BROOD&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Brood refers to the developing young bees, including larvae and pupae, which are cared for by the Worker Bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-bbe65f20246fcdba1ffce44cd00d77cc</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 37}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FORAGING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ACTIVITY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Foraging is the process by which Worker Bees collect nectar, pollen, water, and propolis from the environment outside the Hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-bbe65f20246fcdba1ffce44cd00d77cc</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 37}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HONEY PRODUCTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ACTIVITY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Honey Production is the process by which Worker Bees convert nectar into honey, storing it within the Hive."&lt;SEP&gt;"Honey production is the process of producing honey within the hive, which is influenced by the hive's weight and activity levels."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-bbe65f20246fcdba1ffce44cd00d77cc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3dbda77a0a0cb04439105e3ecd8449b4</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 38}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GLANDS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Glands are organs that develop and mature in the young bee after she emerges from her natal cell."&lt;SEP&gt;"Glands are specialized structures within the Worker Bee's body that produce substances necessary for various hive functions, such as royal jelly and wax."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-bbe65f20246fcdba1ffce44cd00d77cc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9dbacd73c4d0e9e9182787aaaced95eb</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 37}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MUSCLES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Muscles are part of the Worker Bee's body that help in performing various tasks within the Hive, such as building comb and moving honey."&lt;SEP&gt;"Muscles are parts of the young bee that develop and mature after she emerges from her natal cell."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-bbe65f20246fcdba1ffce44cd00d77cc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9dbacd73c4d0e9e9182787aaaced95eb</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 37}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NATAL CELL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Natal Cell is the cell within the Hive where a Worker Bee develops from an egg until she emerges as an adult."&lt;SEP&gt;"Natal Cell is the place where a worker bee hatches and develops until she emerges as an adult."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-bbe65f20246fcdba1ffce44cd00d77cc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9dbacd73c4d0e9e9182787aaaced95eb</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 37}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MATING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Mating is the process by which Drones mate with the Queen Bee, ensuring the continuation of the colony."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-bbe65f20246fcdba1ffce44cd00d77cc</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 34}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;EGG LAYING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ACTIVITY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Egg Laying is the process by which the Queen Bee lays eggs, which develop into new bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-bbe65f20246fcdba1ffce44cd00d77cc</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 33}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GENETIC FACTOR&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Genetic Factor is a biological influence that affects the Worker Bee's capability or inclination to perform certain tasks."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-bbe65f20246fcdba1ffce44cd00d77cc</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 37}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MOTIVATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Motivation is the driving force behind the Worker Bee's actions and behaviors within the Hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-bbe65f20246fcdba1ffce44cd00d77cc</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 37}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ACTIONS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Actions refer to the various tasks and behaviors performed by Worker Bees within the Hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-bbe65f20246fcdba1ffce44cd00d77cc</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 37}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TASKS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Tasks are specific activities that Worker Bees perform, such as brood rearing, foraging, and honey production."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-bbe65f20246fcdba1ffce44cd00d77cc</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 37}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ENVIRONMENT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Environment refers to the external surroundings where Worker Bees gather resources such as nectar and pollen."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-bbe65f20246fcdba1ffce44cd00d77cc</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 37}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ROYAL JELLY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PRODUCT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Royal Jelly is a substance produced by Worker Bees that is fed to the Queen Bee and developing larvae to ensure their growth and health."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-bbe65f20246fcdba1ffce44cd00d77cc</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 37}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BROOD NEST&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Brood Nest is the central area of the hive where worker bees are born and initially develop."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9dbacd73c4d0e9e9182787aaaced95eb</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HOUSE BEE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ROLE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"House Bee is a phase in the life of a worker bee where she performs duties within the hive, including orientation flights."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9dbacd73c4d0e9e9182787aaaced95eb</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FIELD BEE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ROLE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Field Bee is a phase in the life of a worker bee where she performs foraging duties outside the hive."&lt;SEP&gt;"Field Bee is a type of bee that performs regular trips outside the hive for tasks such as foraging and orientation flights."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6b4933e28419676b4dc2c84fef33d751&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9dbacd73c4d0e9e9182787aaaced95eb</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ADULT BEE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ROLE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Adult Bee is a fully developed worker bee that is ready to work almost immediately after emerging from her natal cell."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9dbacd73c4d0e9e9182787aaaced95eb</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INITIAL PERIOD&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TIME_PERIOD"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Initial Period is the brief time after the bee emerges from her natal cell when she focuses on eating and grooming."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9dbacd73c4d0e9e9182787aaaced95eb</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DEBTORS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Debtors are the parties involved in negotiations and transactions, who may enter into a Superior Alternative Transaction.")&lt;SEP&gt;"Debtors refer to the entities involved in a restructuring process, responsible for determining and negotiating alternative transactions."&lt;SEP&gt;"Debtors refer to the parties involved in a financial transaction, specifically mentioned in the context of receiving unsolicited proposals for alternative transactions."&lt;SEP&gt;"Debtors refer to the parties involved in the transaction, responsible for providing notice and entering into alternative transactions."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-fcdcd9d30072864ded5702f89ad5c010&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6b4933e28419676b4dc2c84fef33d751&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-73e41d4fce5a979254140bea80d946f2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-16f0aadafde3c111ee502eb0594b6ba4</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 55}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PREPETITION AGENTS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Prepetition Agents are legal representatives acting on behalf of the Debtors before any petition is filed.")&lt;SEP&gt;"Prepetition Agents are the agents involved before the petition for bankruptcy, assisting in the consultation process for alternative transactions."&lt;SEP&gt;"Prepetition Agents are the agents involved before the petition, responsible for receiving notices and providing consultations."&lt;SEP&gt;"Prepetition Agents are the agents mentioned in the context of receiving notifications about proposed alternative transactions, indicating their role in the financial dealings of the Debtors."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-fcdcd9d30072864ded5702f89ad5c010&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6b4933e28419676b4dc2c84fef33d751&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-73e41d4fce5a979254140bea80d946f2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-16f0aadafde3c111ee502eb0594b6ba4</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 55}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BUSINESS DAYS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Business Days refer to specific working days within which actions must be completed, such as reviewing and commenting on communications."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6b4933e28419676b4dc2c84fef33d751</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PROPOSED ALTERNATIVE TRANSACTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Proposed Alternative Transaction is a suggested transaction that could provide better recovery compared to the original plan or transactions."&lt;SEP&gt;"Proposed Alternative Transaction is an event where the Debtors receive unsolicited proposals from other parties, indicating a potential change in their financial dealings."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6b4933e28419676b4dc2c84fef33d751&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-16f0aadafde3c111ee502eb0594b6ba4</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 55}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ORIENTATION FLIGHTS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Orientation Flights are the flights performed by bees to learn and memorize the layout of their environment, aiding in navigation."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6b4933e28419676b4dc2c84fef33d751</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;REGULAR TRIPS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Regular Trips are the routine foraging missions performed by field bees outside the hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6b4933e28419676b4dc2c84fef33d751</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WING MUSCLES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Wing Muscles are the muscles used by bees for flight, which are exercised during orientation flights."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6b4933e28419676b4dc2c84fef33d751</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PLAN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Plan is a detailed proposal for the restructuring process, outlining the steps and outcomes."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-16f0aadafde3c111ee502eb0594b6ba4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SUPERIOR ALTERNATIVE TRANSACTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Superior Alternative Transaction is a proposed transaction that must be approved by the Board and Prepetition Agents."&lt;SEP&gt;"Superior Alternative Transaction is an alternative transaction that is determined to provide better recovery compared to the original plan or transactions."&lt;SEP&gt;"Superior Alternative Transaction refers to a better deal that would terminate ongoing negotiations or discussions.")</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-fcdcd9d30072864ded5702f89ad5c010&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-73e41d4fce5a979254140bea80d946f2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-16f0aadafde3c111ee502eb0594b6ba4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DEBTORS’ FIDUCIARY DUTIES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Debtors’ fiduciary duties are the legal obligations of the Debtors to act in the best interest of the stakeholders."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-16f0aadafde3c111ee502eb0594b6ba4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CLAIMS AND EQUITY INTERESTS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Claims and Equity Interests refer to the financial interests held by stakeholders in the Debtors."&lt;SEP&gt;"Claims and Equity Interests refer to the rights and interests of the creditors and equity holders in the Debtors."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-73e41d4fce5a979254140bea80d946f2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-16f0aadafde3c111ee502eb0594b6ba4</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 55}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CLAIMS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Claims refer to the rights of creditors to receive payment or compensation from the Debtors."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-16f0aadafde3c111ee502eb0594b6ba4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NOTICE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Notice is the formal communication that includes the material terms and accompanying documentation of a Proposed Alternative Transaction."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-16f0aadafde3c111ee502eb0594b6ba4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MATERIAL TERMS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Material terms refer to the key details of a transaction that are important for stakeholders to know."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-16f0aadafde3c111ee502eb0594b6ba4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CORRESPONDENCE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Correspondence includes any written or electronic communication related to a Proposed Alternative Transaction."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-16f0aadafde3c111ee502eb0594b6ba4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;OUTSIDE LEGAL COUNSEL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Outside legal counsel refers to external legal advisors consulted by the Board."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-16f0aadafde3c111ee502eb0594b6ba4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BOARD’S FIDUCIARY DUTIES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Board’s fiduciary duties are the legal obligations of the Board to act in the best interest of the stakeholders."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-16f0aadafde3c111ee502eb0594b6ba4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BREACHING FIDUCIARY DUTIES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Breaching fiduciary duties refers to failing to act in the best interest of the stakeholders, which could lead to legal consequences."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-16f0aadafde3c111ee502eb0594b6ba4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CONFIRMATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Confirmation is the process of finalizing the Plan or Transactions through court approval."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-16f0aadafde3c111ee502eb0594b6ba4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CONSUMMATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Consummation refers to the completion or execution of a transaction or plan."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-16f0aadafde3c111ee502eb0594b6ba4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PLAN OR TRANSACTIONS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Plan or Transactions refer to the overall restructuring process, including the Plan and specific Transactions."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-16f0aadafde3c111ee502eb0594b6ba4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ENTERING INTO A SUPERIOR ALTERNATIVE TRANSACTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Entering into a Superior Alternative Transaction refers to the action of pursuing a better recovery option."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-16f0aadafde3c111ee502eb0594b6ba4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NEGOTIATING A SUPERIOR ALTERNATIVE TRANSACTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Negotiating a Superior Alternative Transaction refers to the process of discussing and agreeing on a better recovery option."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-16f0aadafde3c111ee502eb0594b6ba4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PROVIDING DUE DILIGENCE IN CONNECTION WITH A SUPERIOR ALTERNATIVE TRANSACTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Providing due diligence in connection with a Superior Alternative Transaction refers to the process of thoroughly investigating the transaction."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-16f0aadafde3c111ee502eb0594b6ba4</data>
</node>
