</node>
<node id="&quot;VOCAL FOLD TRAINING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Vocal fold training involves specific exercises and techniques to enhance vocal abilities."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-295c4464cba2eac03c733df516785973</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VOCAL FOLD FATIGUE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Vocal fold fatigue is the state of tiredness in the vocal folds, which can affect performance."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-295c4464cba2eac03c733df516785973</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VOCAL FOLD HYDRATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Vocal fold hydration is important for maintaining vocal health and preventing strain."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-295c4464cba2eac03c733df516785973</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VOCAL FOLD SUPPORT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Vocal fold support involves proper breathing and posture to provide adequate air flow and control."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-295c4464cba2eac03c733df516785973</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SINGING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ACTIVITY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Singing is a vocal activity driven by text, emphasizing enunciation and electronic amplification of voices. It involves frequent style changes and requires dance skills, with a variable range of musical values."&lt;SEP&gt;"Singing requires a different breathing technique compared to dancing, emphasizing abdominal breathing for better control and performance."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d7d4b0f4dd925d2693c4ec118a27e266&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-df3a4ad39eb32af1c4e7f021a096b02d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VOICES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ACTIVITY"</data>
