  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Styles in singing change frequently, reflecting the diverse nature of performances."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d7d4b0f4dd925d2693c4ec118a27e266</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;UNTRAINED SINGERS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Untrained singers can perform effectively in singing without difficulty, highlighting the accessibility of the activity."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d7d4b0f4dd925d2693c4ec118a27e266</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SONGS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Songs are transposed as needed to fit the performance requirements."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d7d4b0f4dd925d2693c4ec118a27e266</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DANCE SKILLS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"SKILL"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Dance skills are required alongside singing, adding a physical component to the performance."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d7d4b0f4dd925d2693c4ec118a27e266</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PHARYNX&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ANATOMY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Pharynx is a part of the vocal tract crucial for classical singing, particularly in producing and sustaining sound."&lt;SEP&gt;"The pharynx is the part of the throat that connects the mouth and nose to the esophagus and larynx, playing a crucial role in both breathing and singing."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ec12e59f09a5549285ad21ffed9bbbd6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d7d4b0f4dd925d2693c4ec118a27e266</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PASSAGGIO&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Passaggio refers to the transition point in a singer's voice where the registers (chest and head) meet, often requiring specific techniques to navigate smoothly."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d7d4b0f4dd925d2693c4ec118a27e266</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MODE 1&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"VOCAL TECHNIQUE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Mode 1, also known as thyroarytenoid [TA] dominant, is a vocal fold vibration pattern used more frequently in singing."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d7d4b0f4dd925d2693c4ec118a27e266</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ELECTRONIC AMPLIFICATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Electronic amplification enhances the voices during singing, allowing for better projection and clarity."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d7d4b0f4dd925d2693c4ec118a27e266</data>
</node>
