</node>
<node id="&quot;TEXT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONTENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Text is the driving force behind singing, with enunciation being a dominant factor."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d7d4b0f4dd925d2693c4ec118a27e266</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SPEECH APPROACH&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNIQUE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The speech approach to singing maintains a relaxed pharynx similar to speaking, enhancing naturalness and ease."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d7d4b0f4dd925d2693c4ec118a27e266</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PHARYNGEAL REGION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"SINGING"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The pharyngeal region is similar to speech during singing."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d7d4b0f4dd925d2693c4ec118a27e266</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LARYNX POSITION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"SINGING"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The larynx is in the mid or high position during singing."</data>
