</node>
<node id="&quot;MOUTH SHAPE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"SINGING"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The mouth shape is horizontal during singing."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d7d4b0f4dd925d2693c4ec118a27e266</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FEMALES VOWELS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"SINGING"</data>
  <data key="d1">"In females, most vowels have a 'brighter' color created by more chest register or altered resonance."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d7d4b0f4dd925d2693c4ec118a27e266</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MALES VOWELS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"SINGING"</data>
  <data key="d1">"In males, the 'brighter' color is maintained due to less modification or covering of vowels at the high passaggio."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d7d4b0f4dd925d2693c4ec118a27e266</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VIBRATO&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Vibrato is a technique used in singing, though not always necessary or appropriate, adding a vibratory quality to the sound."&lt;SEP&gt;"Vibrato is not always used or appropriate in singing."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ec12e59f09a5549285ad21ffed9bbbd6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d7d4b0f4dd925d2693c4ec118a27e266</data>
