<node id="&quot;MONOD'S TEAM&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Monod's team includes researchers who collaborated with Monod in studying bacterial genetics and enzyme regulation."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5b2b3ed969d34b9c50bfc385bc325780</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;Β-GALACTOSIDASE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"β-galactosidase is an enzyme whose production is regulated in bacteria, and mutations affecting its production were studied by Monod and his team."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5b2b3ed969d34b9c50bfc385bc325780</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FRANÇOIS JACOB&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"François Jacob is a scientist who later collaborated with Monod to understand the regulation of β-galactosidase, challenging Monod's initial hypothesis."&lt;SEP&gt;"François Jacob is a scientist who originally planned to become a surgeon but became a researcher after being wounded in Normandy during World War II. He worked with Monod to develop methods for studying gene regulation."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9762f0ff2690cb73681a54a57f2e9170&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b2b3ed969d34b9c50bfc385bc325780</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BACTERIA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Bacteria are the subjects of study for Monod and his team, specifically focusing on mutations that affect β-galactosidase production."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5b2b3ed969d34b9c50bfc385bc325780</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LACTOSE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Lactose is a sugar used as an inducer for β-galactosidase production in bacteria, and its presence affects the regulation of the enzyme."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5b2b3ed969d34b9c50bfc385bc325780</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ENZYME&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Enzyme refers to the β-galactosidase enzyme, which is produced in bacteria and regulated by genetic mechanisms."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5b2b3ed969d34b9c50bfc385bc325780</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GENETIC APPROACH&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Genetic approach involves studying the effects of mutations on gene expression and enzyme production in bacteria."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5b2b3ed969d34b9c50bfc385bc325780</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INDUCER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Inducer is a substance that activates the production of β-galactosidase, and its role in regulating enzyme production was initially misunderstood by Monod."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5b2b3ed969d34b9c50bfc385bc325780</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MUTATIONS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Mutations refer to changes in the genetic material of bacteria that affect the production of β-galactosidase."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5b2b3ed969d34b9c50bfc385bc325780</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;REGULATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Regulation refers to the control of gene expression and enzyme production in bacteria, particularly the on/off switching of β-galactosidase."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5b2b3ed969d34b9c50bfc385bc325780</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WAR&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The War refers to World War II, which influenced François Jacob's career path."&lt;SEP&gt;"The war influenced François Jacob's career path, originally planning to become a surgeon but later collaborating with Monod."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9762f0ff2690cb73681a54a57f2e9170&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b2b3ed969d34b9c50bfc385bc325780</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SURGEON&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ROLE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Surgeon is a medical profession that François Jacob considered before the war."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5b2b3ed969d34b9c50bfc385bc325780</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NEW PLAYER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The new player refers to the gene that disrupts the regulation of β-galactosidase, which was initially misunderstood by Monod."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5b2b3ed969d34b9c50bfc385bc325780</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CONSTITUTIVE MUTATIONS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Constitutive mutations are a type of mutation that causes the β-galactosidase enzyme to be produced continuously, regardless of lactose presence."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5b2b3ed969d34b9c50bfc385bc325780</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ON/OFF REGULATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"On/off regulation refers to the normal mechanism of β-galactosidase production being turned on or off in response to lactose."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5b2b3ed969d34b9c50bfc385bc325780</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INTERNAL INDUCER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Internal Inducer is a substance predicted to be produced when normal and mutant genes are mixed together, as part of the enzyme regulation process."&lt;SEP&gt;"Internal inducer is a substance produced by bacteria that Monod initially hypothesized to activate β-galactosidase production."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9762f0ff2690cb73681a54a57f2e9170&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b2b3ed969d34b9c50bfc385bc325780</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MUTANT BACTERIA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Mutant bacteria are bacteria that have undergone genetic changes affecting β-galactosidase production."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5b2b3ed969d34b9c50bfc385bc325780</data>
</node>
