  <data key="d6">chunk-c8df3b15e9b2d107be4903da602ae638</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CHEST REGISTER&quot;" target="&quot;MIX/BELT SOUND&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Mix/belt sound also involves the use of the chest register, particularly important for reaching lower notes required in modern musicals."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-c8df3b15e9b2d107be4903da602ae638</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CHEST REGISTER&quot;" target="&quot;HEAD REGISTER&quot;">
  <data key="d4">23.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Chest register and head register are separate vocal registers that can be isolated and then blended or mixed for a versatile vocal sound."&lt;SEP&gt;"Head and chest registers are both important in music theater, with lighter-voiced singers using more head mix quality and larger-voiced singers favoring chest mix quality."&lt;SEP&gt;"Head register and chest register are separate vocal registers that can be isolated and then blended or mixed for a versatile vocal sound."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-8090fb68c19eabe51835bf8e056411f4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c8df3b15e9b2d107be4903da602ae638</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
