  <data key="d5">"Insects are part of the Animal Kingdom, including bees, wasps, and other similar-looking species, often confused with each other."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-314ae8e8df408e418608c7ade21dd41b</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;INSECTS&quot;" target="&quot;SUBORDER&quot;">
  <data key="d4">6.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Insects are classified at the suborder level, where honey bees and yellow jackets are related, leading to some confusion."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-314ae8e8df408e418608c7ade21dd41b</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;INSECTS&quot;" target="&quot;COLONIES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Insects live in colonies, often confused with each other due to similar appearances."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-314ae8e8df408e418608c7ade21dd41b</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;INSECTS&quot;" target="&quot;SMITH&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Smith speculates about the role of insects in controlling the tree's greenery, indicating his ecological knowledge."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-99579aca64585be1bf162fb8cfb56ecb</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SUMMER OUTINGS&quot;" target="&quot;OUTDOOR ACTIVITIES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Outdoor Activities, particularly during summer, involve encountering insects, leading to frequent misidentifications."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-314ae8e8df408e418608c7ade21dd41b</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;NEAR EAST&quot;" target="&quot;SETTLERS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
